  abstract = {Report on focus groups with parents on their participation in school life. Schools where the principal and management are open to parent participation, i.e. schools that have opened their doors to parents enjoy the highest rate of parent participation in school life. In such schools, parents feel welcome and mainly go to the schools to inquire about their children. These schools tend to support most parents' initiatives and consult them on many important issues. Parents see the principal as the most important link for parent participation. Roma are completely excluded from school life. Only one out of 16 Roma parents from the two focus groups had ever heard of a parents council. Their greatest problem remains the unjust attitude towards their children and poor relations with parents of non-Roma children. Parents of children with special needs are comparatively more involved in school life due to the lack of professional staff at schools. Parents rarely mention positive examples of participation.},
